{"key":"post-12723777","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12723777</id>\n<content>Spent coffee grinds are what you want to use.&amp;nbsp; After they've brewed a pot of coffee, they can be mixed with the coir and/or verm and pasteurized.&amp;nbsp; Don't use coffee grinds right out of the can.&amp;nbsp; Your substrate will contaminate.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don't use coir without pasteurizing.&amp;nbsp; In addition, a mixture of 50/50 coir-verm makes an excellent substrate.&amp;nbsp; Verm has food for fungi too in the form of minerals.&amp;nbsp; It's also considered a 'fertilizer' for plants, so adding verm to any bulk substrate makes it better.&amp;nbsp; Gypsum is also an excellent mineral additive.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12728797</next>\n<prev>12723757</prev>\n<first>12723451</first>\n<last>12728797</last>\n<when>1276232225</when>\n<utime>06/11/10 07:57 AM</utime>\n</post>"}